                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/7866</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                            <persName type="to">Simpich</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-24T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 24, 1916, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department informed [Norton] Hand under sentence death.</p>
                <p>Urgently request appropriate authorities not to execute sentence until
                    opportunity is afforded this Government for investigation.</p>
                <p>Make such investigation of case as is practicable and inform Department at
                    earliest possible date.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
